neutron_lib/api/definitions/classificati.message:
After reading again the spec and start playing with it in devstack, I come to this:

If I understand well this is a hierarchical object structure:
-|
 |__classification_groups
 |        |__classifications
 |        |__classifications
 |
 |__classification_type

This is the same like the QoS structure, so I suggest something like this:
RESOURCE_ATTRIBUTE_MAP = {
 CLASSIFICATION_GROUPS: {.....},
 CLASSIFICATION_TYPES: {....}
}
SUB_RESOURCE_ATTRIBUTE_MAP = {
 CLASSIFICATIONS: {'parent':CLASSIFICATION_GROUPS, .....}
}

I understand that the current API extension in neutron-classifier has this api structure (see: https://opendev.org/x/neutron-classifier/src/branch/master/neutron_classifier/extensions/classification.py#L44-L51), but:
* this seems to be more "neutronic" for me,
* follows the logical hierarchic structure of the resources.

